    <h2>What is Tera.TF?</h2>
    <p>TeraGaming was founded by TerabyteNation, and it's website was developed by
      <a href="http://www.steamcommunity.com/id/TerabyteNation">TerabyteNation</a>,
      <a href="http://www.steamcommunity.com/id/eqazec">eqazec</a>, and
      <a href="http://www.steamcommunity.com/id/redjazz96/">redjazz96</a>.</p>
    <p>Tera.TF is a website that was made by fans of Team Fortress 2. This site was created as a place that has a variety of TF2 related activites, including normal gameplay, competitive, trading, custom community content (mods, maps, SFM stuff, etc.), and several other features. Tera.TF provides forums and community profiles so users can interact with each other. Tera.TF has a very active staff that works to keep the site clean, and provides support to community members.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="contentbox">
    <h2>Development Information</h2>
    <p>This website was written in Ruby, and it uses a framework for web development called <a href="http://rubyonrails.org/">Ruby on Rails</a>. Tera.TF utilizes Steam OpenID for functions such as the login page, and also utilizes the SteamAPI for features such as backpack viewing, etc. The forums are powered by an amazing engine for Rails called <a href="https://github.com/radar/forem">Forem.</a></p>
  </div>

